-- Japanese Sold Net 804.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-05-22T23:51:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-22/japanese-sold-net-804-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 17 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 804.4 billion yen ($7.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 136.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 102.1 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 1043.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 17.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 716 billion yen in stocks, and bought 453.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1187.5
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
